seal     : If the whisper lattice writes inward and quiet, the loud lattice speaks outward and across. A signed mesh of the fourteen domains: each domain holds its own keypair and its own chain, a pulse is signed with a private key and verified with the public one, it gossips hop-by-hop across the mesh, and it only commits when a quorum of domains has verified it. Trust without a center.
